  "prompt": "What are some songs that make you cry?",
  "response": "Songs that evoke strong emotions and can make people cry often address themes of love, loss, heartache, and resilience. Here are some examples that many people find deeply moving:\n\n1. **\"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton** - Written after the tragic loss of Clapton's son, this song's poignant lyrics and somber melody can resonate deeply with listeners.\n\n2. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen (and covered by many artists)** - This song\u2019s hauntingly beautiful melody and introspective lyrics can touch the soul, especially in heartfelt renditions by artists like Jeff Buckley.\n\n3. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele** - A ballad about a past relationship and moving on, Adele\u2019s powerful vocals and emotionally charged delivery make this song a tear-jerker.\n\n4. **\"Fix You\" by Coldplay** - The comforting and hopeful message mixed with the swelling instrumentation can bring listeners to tears, especially during the climax.\n\n5. **\"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron** - With its melancholic tone and lyrics about longing and regret, this song can feel incredibly emotional.\n\n6. **\"Fast Car\" by Tracy Chapman** - A story of dreams, escape, and reality that can strike a chord with many listeners.\n\n7. **\"Hurt\" by Johnny Cash (cover of Nine Inch Nails)** - Johnny Cash\u2019s raw rendition of this song, combined with his weathered voice and the themes of regret and pain, makes it deeply touching.\n\n8. **\"Yesterday\" by The Beatles** - Reflecting on loss and longing, this classic evokes nostalgia and sadness.\n\n9. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston (written by Dolly Parton)** - A powerful ballad about farewell and enduring love, which can be incredibly moving when combined with Houston\u2019s soaring vocals.\n\n10. **\"Say Something\" by A Great Big World and Christina Aguilera** - The desperate pleading and emotional delivery make this song resonate with anyone who has experienced the pain of letting go.\n\nThese songs are just a few examples, but there's a vast array of music out there that can evoke deep emotional responses depending on personal experiences and memories.",
